Five people died when a truck collided with a matatu on Nakuru-Kericho highway early on Sunday morning. The crash took place at about 2.30 am at Chebwor village near the Londiani junction. The matatu was on its way to Nakuru from Kericho. "They all died at the scene," Londiani OCPD Joseph Odipo said, adding that those injured were taken to Londioni and Kericho hospitals. Police took the bodies to Molo sub-county hospital mortuary. Click here for the latest political news 